In 1967 I was the Senior Advisor to the ARVN 7th Cav. Regt in the Hue and Quang Tre area. I had two Ausses on my team [I was asked by the Chief of Ausse Armor] and they were fine soldiers.<br>
  In the Hue compond, I was honored to associate with the Ausses there.  They could outdrink, outfight and outxxxx almost everyone.  Super troops. Their Army must have screened them for they were all exceptional.  Next door to me was the first Aussie field grade officer to win the VC.<br>
  One man, name McKnee[?] was in a sub-sector that was overrun.  They found him, surrounded by bodies, calmly cleaning his rifle. <br>
   He gave me his Bush Hat, and I still have it.<br>
   Austrailia should be most proud of the men they sent--a gallant bunch---if I ever have to fight again, I hope they are on my flank.
